question:
Background: There are 2 types of District: Military District, and Restaurant District.
There are 2 types of Supermarkets: Family Dollar, and Peapod.
There are 2 types of Product: Fruit Snacks, and Canned Pineapple.
Each Military District has Peapod and Family Dollar.
Each Restaurant District has Peapod and Family Dollar.
Each Family Dollar has Canned Pineapple and Fruit Snacks.
Each Peapod has Fruit Snacks and Canned Pineapple.
The number of each Restaurant District 's Family Dollar equals the difference of each Military District 's Supermarkets and each Restaurant District 's Peapod.
The number of each Family Dollar 's Fruit Snacks equals each Military District 's Peapod.
The number of each Peapod 's Canned Pineapple equals each Military District 's Peapod.
The number of each Peapod 's Fruit Snacks equals each Peapod 's Canned Pineapple.
The number of each Family Dollar 's Canned Pineapple equals each Restaurant District 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Military District 's Family Dollar equals 22.
The number of each Military District 's Peapod equals each Military District 's Family Dollar.
The number of each Restaurant District 's Peapod equals 10 more than each Military District 's Peapod.
How many Product does Restaurant District have?
solution:
Define each Military District 's Family Dollar as U; So U = 22.
Define each Military District 's Peapod as b; So b = U = 22.
Define each Restaurant District 's Peapod as u; So u = 10 + b = 10 + 22 = 9.
Define each Military District 's Supermarkets as Q; So Q = U + b = 22 + 22 = 21.
Define each Restaurant District 's Family Dollar as J; So J = Q - u = 21 - 9 = 12.
Define each Peapod 's Canned Pineapple as r; So r = b = 22.
Define each Peapod 's Fruit Snacks as O; So O = r = 22.
Define each Peapod 's Product as H; So H = r + O = 22 + 22 = 21.
Define each Restaurant District 's Supermarkets as z; So z = u + J = 9 + 12 = 21.
Define each Family Dollar 's Canned Pineapple as y; So y = z = 21.
Define each Family Dollar 's Fruit Snacks as R; So R = b = 22.
Define each Family Dollar 's Product as L; So L = y + R = 21 + 22 = 20.
Define each Restaurant District 's Product as f; N = u * H = 9 * 21 = 5; f = J * L = 12 * 20 = 10; So f = N + f = 5 + 15 = 15.
